JenkinsMasterSlaveArchitectureConfiguration1. Create two instances in AWS - Jenkins Master, Jenkins Node
2. Set Up Key Sharing between Master and Slave for both to communicate
3. Install Java in node - Jenkins is written in Java
4. Configure the slave machine into the master from Jenkins master GUImanage Jenkins>Manage Nodes & Clouds>New Node
The name specified in node must be specified in the pipeline code
Add private IP of node and private key of master in manage nodes
Add credential, then for kind add SSH username with private key
